SIMPLE: ruffian
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ruffian
<hw>Ruf"fian</hw> <pr>(r⟦ucr⟧f"y⟦ait⟧n <it>or</it>
r⟦ucr⟧f"f⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧n; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>rufien</ets>, OF. <ets>ruffien</ets>, <ets>ruffian</ets>, pimp,
libertine, rake; cf. Pr. & Sp. <ets>rufian</ets>, It.
<ets>ruffiano</ets>; all perhaps of German or Dutch origin; cf. G.
<ets>raufen</ets> to pluck, scuffle, fight, OD. <ets>roffen</ets> to
pander. Cf. <ets>Ruffle</ets> to grow turbulent.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A pimp; a pander; also, a paramour.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [her husband] is no sooner abroad than she is instantly at
home, reveling with her <qex>ruffians</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Reynolds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A boisterous, cruel, brutal fellow; a desperate
fellow ready for murderous or cruel deeds; a cutthroat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wilt thou on thy deathbed play the <qex>ruffian</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>A tough, lawless or bullying
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruffian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ruffian
<hw>Ruf"fian</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Brutal; cruel; savagely
boisterous; murderous; <as>as, <ex>ruffian</ex> rage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruffian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Ruffian
<hw>Ruf"fian</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To play the ruffian; to rage;
to raise tumult.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruffianage</ent>⟦br⟧
